{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly for the basis of hamming weight two, we can restrict the unitary to a N 2 × N 2 matrix.",
    "Since the reduced matrix conserves its unitary property and has only real values, these are orthogonal matrices.",
    "More generally, we can think of such hamming weight preserving circuits with N qubits as block-diagonal unitaries that act separately on N + 1 subspaces, where the k-th subspace is defined by all computational basis states with hamming weight equal to k. The dimension of these subspaces is equal to N k. There exist many possibilities for building a quantum orthogonal layer, each with different properties.",
    "The Pyramid circuit, proposed in [5], is composed of exactly N (N -1)/2 RBS gates.",
    "This circuit requires only adjacent qubit connectivity, which is the case for most superconducting qubit hardware."
  ]
}